iv><div class=\"pt-4 md:pt-10\"><div><article id=\"article-985605e8-5bd9-3587-9366-8286a60cea66\"><div><div class=\"mx-auto md:px-10 md:max-w-[1220px]\"></div><div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 lg:gap-x-0 mx-auto md:px-10 md:max-w-[1220px] md:grid-cols-[[main-start]_1fr_[main-end_right-start]_min-content_[right-end]] lg:!gap-x-8\"><div class=\"md:col-main\" data-i13n-boundary=\"true\"><div><div><div><div class=\"grid grid-cols-[[fullbleed-start_body-start]_minmax(auto,750px)_[body-end_fullbleed-end]]\"><figure class=\"relative col-body mb-4\"><div class=\"relative overflow-hidden fig-image-round left-1/2 w-screen -translate-x-1/2 md:left-0 md:w-auto md:translate-x-0\" style=\"aspect-ratio:1.7777777777777777\"><img alt=\"\" fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"auto\" data-nimg=\"fill\" class=\"object-cover object-center\" style=\"position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/Fu_eueCiDrkMWGfIibN0QA--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTEyNDI7aD03NzY-/https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-02/cc2274e0-6b09-11eb-bf5e-f259e4d54fff\"><button aria-label=\"View larger image\" class=\"group absolute bottom-3 right-3 size-10 md:size-[50px] lg:inset-0 lg:size-full lg:bg-transparent\" data-ylk=\"elm:expand;itc:1;sec:image-lightbox;slk:lightbox-open;\" data-yga=\"{&quot;yLinkElement&quot;:&quot;expand&quot;,&quot;yModuleName&quot;:&quot;image-lightbox&quot;,&quot;yLinkText&quot;:&quot;lightbox-open&quot;,&quot;yHasCommerce&quot;:false}\"><span class=\"absolute bottom-0 right-0 rounded-full bg-white p-3 opacity-100 shadow-elevation-3 transition-opacity duration-300 group-hover:block group-hover:opacity-100 md:p-[17px] lg:bottom-6 lg:right-6 lg:bg-white/90 lg:p-5 lg:opacity-0 lg:shadow-none\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 22 22\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"size-4 lg:size-6\" width=\"22\" height=\"22\"><path d=\"M12.372.92c0-.506.41-.916.915-.916L21 0l-.004 7.712a.917.917 0 0 1-1.832 0V3.183l-6.827 6.828-1.349-1.348 6.828-6.828h-4.529a.915.915 0 0 1-.915-.915M1.835 17.816l6.828-6.828 1.349 1.349-6.829 6.827h4.529a.915.915 0 0 1 0 1.831L0 21l.004-7.713a.916.916 0 0 1 1.831 0z\"></path></svg></span></button><dialog aria-label=\"Modal Dialog\" aria-modal=\"true\" class=\"fixed inset-0 z-[4] size-full max-h-none max-w-none bg-white hidden\"></dialog></div><figcaption class=\"relative text-[0.875rem]/[1.25rem] figure-caption mt-1 line-clamp-2 mt-2.5 md:mt-2 pr-2.5\"><div><span class=\"[&amp;_p]:inline\"></span><span>Aurora</span></div></figcaption></figure></div></div><div class=\"grid grid-cols-article-mobile md:grid-cols-article lg:max-w-[750px] drop-cap\" data-article-body=\"true\"><p class=\"col-body mb-4 leading-7 text-[18px] md:leading-8 break-words min-w-0 charcoal-color\">A mere two months after acquiring <a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/uber-atg-sale-aurora-221855364.html\" data-ylk=\"slk:Uber’s self-driving car unit;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" data-yga=\"{&quot;yLinkElement&quot;:&quot;context_link&quot;,&quot;yModuleName&quot;:&quot;content-canvas&quot;,&quot;yLinkText&quot;:&quot;Uber’s self-driving car unit&quot;}\" class=\"link \">Uber’s self-driving car unit</a> (and a $400 million investment from the company), autonomous vehicle startup Aurora is partnering with the world’s largest automaker. On Tuesday, the company announced a <a href=\"https://aurora.tech/blog/mobility-for-all-launching-the-aurora-driver-on-ride-hailing\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-ylk=\"slk:partnership;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" data-yga=\"{&quot;yLinkElement&quot;:&quot;context_link&quot;,&quot;yModuleName&quot;:&quot;content-canvas&quot;,&quot;yLinkText&quot;:&quot;partnership&quot;}\" class=\"link \">partnership</a> with Toyota and Japanese auto parts supplier Denso (via <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/2/9/22274640/toyota-aurora-denso-self-driving-car-robotaxi\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-ylk=\"slk:The Verge;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" data-yga=\"{&quot;yLinkElement&quot;:&quot;context_link&quot;,&quot;yModuleName&quot;:&quot;content-canvas&quot;,&quot;yLinkText&quot;:&quot;The Verge&quot;}\" class=\"link \"><em>The Verge</em></a>) that will see the three firms work together to develop and test vehicles with Aurora’s Driver technology. They’ll first integrate the hardware and software into a fleet of Toyota Sienna minivans before deploying it within a full-scale robotaxai service.</p><p class=\"col-body mb-4 leading-7 text-[18px] md:leading-8 break-words min-w-0 charcoal-color\">“By the end of 2021, we expect to have designed, built and begun testing an initial fleet of these Siennas near our areas of development,” the company said. “It brings our companies together to lay the groundwork for the mass-production, launch and support of these vehicles with Toyota on ride-hailing networks, including Uber’s, over the next few years.”</p><p class=\"col-body mb-4 leading-7 text-[18px] md:leading-8 break-words min-w-0 charcoal-color\">Today’s announcement is an important one for Toyota in so far as the company hasn’t had a lot to show yet for all of the effort it has put into developing its own autonomous vehicle technologies. At the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo, the automaker said it would allow people to ride cars equipped with its <a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/2019-10-24-toyota-self-driving-car-test-tokyo-olympics.html\" data-ylk=\"slk:Level-4 “Chauffeur” technology;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" data-yga=\"{&quot;yLinkElement&quot;:&quot;context_link&quot;,&quot;yModuleName&quot;:&quot;content-canvas&quot;,&quot;yLinkText&quot;:&quot;Level-4 “Chauffeur” technology&quot;}\" class=\"link \">Level-4 “Chauffeur” technology</a>, among other <a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/2019-10-09-toyota-e-palette-tokyo-olympics-2020.html\" data-ylk=\"slk:self-driving vehicle projects;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" data-yga=\"{&quot;yLinkElement&quot;:&quot;context_link&quot;,&quot;yModuleName&quot;:&quot;content-canvas&quot;,&quot;yLinkText&quot;:&quot;self-driving vehicle projects&quot;}\" class=\"link \">self-driving vehicle projects</a>. Those demos have had to wait thanks to the coronavirus pandemic. We also have yet to see Toyota integrate “<a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/2019-01-07-toyota-self-driving-lexus-two-autonomous-systems-at-once.html\" data-ylk=\"slk:Guardian;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" data-yga=\"{&quot;yLinkElement&quot;:&quot;context_link&quot;,&quot;yModuleName&quot;:&quot;content-canvas&quot;,&quot;yLinkText&quot;:&quot;Guardian&quot;}\" class=\"link \">Guardian</a>,” the driver-assist system it announced alongside Chauffeur in 2019, into a production vehicle. At the time, that was something Toyota said it would offer soon and to any automaker that wanted to take advantage of it.</p></div></div></div></div><div class=\"contents\"></div><div class=\"md:col-main grid grid-cols-article-mobile md:grid-cols-article lg:max-w-[750px]\"><div class=\"no-scrollbar col-body mx-4 mb-8 mt-2.5 overflow-x-scroll whitespace-nowrap md:mx-0 md:max-w-[750px] md:overflow-x-visible\"><div class=\"pointer-events-none absolute right-3.5 h-6 w-16 bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent to-white md:hidden\"></div><div class=\"mx-auto max-w-screen-sm\"><ul class=\"inline-flex text-xs md:text-sm\"><li class=\"mr-6\"><a data-ylk=\"elm:corp;itc:0;sec:footer;\" data-yga=\"{&quot;yLinkElement&quot;:&quot;corp&quot;,&quot;yModuleName&quot;:&quot;footer&quot;,&quot;yHasCommerce&quot;:false}\" href=\"https://legal.yahoo.com/us/en/yahoo/privacy/adinfo/index.html\" class=\"text-[14px]/[17.5px] text-dolphin hover:underline\">About our ads</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></article><div class=\"mx-auto mb-6 mt-5 min-h-[250px] max-w-full items-center justify-center md:min-h-[90px]\" id=\"_R_rb4ilfeiv5tilbH1_\" ollre0pps=\"\"><div class=\"hidden\" id=\"_R_rb4ilfeiv5tilb_\"></div><div class=\